---
import '../styles/globals.css';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <meta name="description" content="convertFlow privacy policy — how we handle your files and data." />
  <title>Privacy — convertFlow</title>
  <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
  <script is:inline>
    (function() {
      const t = localStorage.getItem('dataprep-theme');
      document.documentElement.setAttribute('data-theme', t === 'light' ? 'light' : 'dark');
    })();
  </script>
</head>
<body>
  <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <a href="/">dataprep</a>
    <span aria-hidden="true">›</span>
    <span aria-current="page">privacy</span>
  </nav>

  <main>
    <h1>Privacy — how convertFlow handles your data</h1>
    <p class="meta">Last updated: 2026-05-12 · 3 min read</p>

    <h2>What we do with your files</h2>
    <p>Files you open, paste, or upload are processed <strong>entirely in your browser</strong>. Parsing libraries (pdf-parse, mammoth, xlsx, tesseract.js) run as WebAssembly / JavaScript modules loaded into your browser tab — they never see a server. No file content, filename, or extracted text is transmitted anywhere, logged, or stored on our infrastructure.</p>

    <h2>Local storage</h2>
    <p>convertFlow persists your in-progress work to your browser's localStorage so it survives page reloads. All keys begin with <code>dataprep</code>:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><code>dataprep-editor-state-v1</code> — open files, active file, split-pane state. Files larger than 3MB are kept in session only.</li>
      <li><code>dataprep-convert-state-v1</code> — dataset files, preset, format settings.</li>
      <li><code>dataprep-chunk-state-v1</code> — chunk strategy, embedder, source.</li>
      <li><code>dataprep:appSettings</code> — your editor / convert / privacy preferences.</li>
      <li><code>dataprep:utilities-state-v1</code> — per-utility input state.</li>
      <li><code>dataprep:hf-token</code> — only if you check "remember on this device" when pushing to Hugging Face Hub.</li>
      <li><code>dataprep-theme</code>, <code>dataprep:tour-seen</code>, <code>dataprep:chunk-show-overlap</code> — UI preferences.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>You can clear everything via <strong>Settings → Privacy → Clear all stored data</strong>. This removes every <code>dataprep*</code> key and reloads the page.</p>

    <h2>When data leaves your browser</h2>
    <p>There are only two situations where convertFlow makes a network request with your data:</p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Push to Hugging Face Hub</strong> — when you explicitly click <strong>↑ HF Hub</strong> on the Convert toolbar, the dataset you've chosen plus your HF write token are sent to <code>huggingface.co</code> via the Hugging Face Commits API. You can clear the saved token any time from Settings → Privacy → "Clear HF Hub token". Nothing else is sent unless you trigger that action.</li>
      <li><strong>Anonymous analytics</strong> — page views and aggregate event counts are sent to Plausible (cookieless, no PII, EU-hosted). You can disable all analytics via <strong>Settings → Privacy → Anonymous telemetry</strong>.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>What we log</h2>
    <p>We do not run a server-side parsing endpoint. Plausible records pageviews and a small set of product-usage events without PII or cookies. Cloudflare may log IP addresses per their standard edge logging — see Cloudflare's privacy policy for details.</p>

    <h2>Libraries used in-browser</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>pdf-parse / pdfjs-dist</strong> — PDF text extraction (WASM in your tab)</li>
      <li><strong>mammoth</strong> — DOCX text extraction</li>
      <li><strong>xlsx</strong> — XLSX text extraction</li>
      <li><strong>tesseract.js</strong> — OCR for image inputs (WASM in your tab)</li>
      <li><strong>monaco-editor</strong> — the code editor surface</li>
      <li><strong>js-tiktoken</strong> — token estimation</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Third parties</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Cloudflare</strong> — static asset hosting (no application data passes through Cloudflare functions).</li>
      <li><strong>Plausible</strong> — privacy-friendly, cookieless analytics. No PII collected, no cross-site tracking. EU-hosted. Opt-out available in Settings.</li>
      <li><strong>Hugging Face</strong> — only contacted when you click "Push to HF Hub" with your token. Your dataset is uploaded directly to the repo you specify.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Your data rights</h2>
    <p>Because convertFlow does not store your data on any server, there is nothing for us to delete on your behalf — clearing your browser's localStorage (or using the in-app "Clear all stored data" button) fully removes your data. If you've pushed a dataset to Hugging Face, you can delete the repo from your Hugging Face account.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions, privacy requests, or feedback: <a href="mailto:support@quakkainfo.com">support@quakkainfo.com</a></p>
  </main>

  <footer class="page-footer">
    <a href="/">← back to tool</a>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>

<style>
  body { margin: 0; padding: 0; }

  .breadcrumb {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    padding: 12px 24px;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--ink-dim);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', ui-monospace, monospace;
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: var(--ink-dim);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .breadcrumb a:hover { color: var(--ink); }

  main {
    max-width: 72ch;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 48px 24px;
    font-family: 'Inter Tight', system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  h1 {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', ui-monospace, monospace;
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 8px;
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  h2 {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', ui-monospace, monospace;
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin: 36px 0 8px;
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  .meta {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--ink-dim);
    margin: 0 0 40px;
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', ui-monospace, monospace;
  }

  p, li { color: var(--ink); }

  ul {
    padding-left: 20px;
    margin: 8px 0 16px;
  }

  li { margin-bottom: 6px; }

  a { color: var(--accent); }
  a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

  strong { font-weight: 500; color: var(--ink); }

  .page-footer {
    max-width: 72ch;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 24px 48px;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', ui-monospace, monospace;
  }

  .page-footer a {
    color: var(--ink-dim);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .page-footer a:hover { color: var(--ink); }
</style>
